   <titles>
      <title>Addition and Scalar Multiplication of Vectors</title>
      <plain.title>Addition, Scalar Multiplication</plain.title>
   </titles>
   <intro>
      <block>
         <block.body>
            <para>
               <para.body>Vectors can be added and they can be multiplied by a number. Vector addition corresponds to concatenating representing arrows, and multiplying a vector by a number corresponds to rescaling the length of a representing arrow. In this section we introduce both of these operations, how to compute effectively with these operations, and how to apply these operations in practical problems.</para.body>
            </para>
         </block.body>
      </block>
   </intro>
